{
  "stem": "9503.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I-- I went from bed to bed, and I looked, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] and it looked like some of the pictures that are in some of the books now.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then, somehow or other, my mother found out that I had gotten in there and that-- that I had used my privileged-- what do you call it-- job, and there was much stricter supervision after that from the orphanage about where I would spend my-- my free time.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[SIGHS] But somehow or other, I-- you know, we both were looking for my father.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "See, the funny thing is I don't remember any women.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I only remember men.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were lying in beds in-- in-- in the typical three-tier beds.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Tears.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't cry.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I still don't cry much, very, very little.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I found a-- a diary that I started in '47, and I described, when we came to America, that my girlfriend was crying.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I wrote in this diary, 'and I can't cry.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Isn't that crazy?' [PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] It was just-- you know, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it was a horror picture, and I still see that.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I still see the-- the carts that came off the train with people on them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] maybe that's the kind of thing a child shouldn't see.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 10 SECONDS] I can't say that much more about that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] No.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother always kept a bread in reserve.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She saved up enough to have one bread.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And somehow or other, she used that one then and was able to replace it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was always a new bread that she had in reserve, waiting for my father to come back.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
